</section>
<header class="article-header">
<div class="article-IDRPromoWrap">
</div>
<figure >
<a href="/podcast/60-second-science/">
<img src="/sciam/cache/file/BFD79196-D190-42E6-928E585CE12EFA25.gif" alt="60-Second Science">
</a>
</figure>
<h1 class="article-title">
Cutting Hormone Could Trip Jetlag
</h1>
<div class="article-dek">
Mice insensitive to the hormone vasopressin recovered from a light-dark time shift much faster than did other rodents. Sophie Bushwick reports.
</div>
<div class="article-author article-date">
Oct 15, 2013
</div>
<div class="article-socialVertical">
<div id="shareFloat">
<a target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode/cutting-hormone-could-trip-jetlag-13-10-15/&amp;text=Cutting Hormone Could Trip Jetlag"><i class="icon-twitter icon-large"></i></a>
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?p[url]=http://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode/cutting-hormone-could-trip-jetlag-13-10-15/"><i class="icon-facebook icon-large"></i></a>
<a target="_blank" href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode/cutting-hormone-could-trip-jetlag-13-10-15/"><i class="icon-googleplus icon-large"></i></a>
<a target="_blank" class="reddit" href="http://www.reddit.com/submit" onclick="window.open('http://www.reddit.com/submit?url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode/cutting-hormone-could-trip-jetlag-13-10-15/&newwindow=1', 'external'); return false"><i class="icon-reddit"></i></a>
</div>
<script type="text/javascript">
